org.apache.river.test.spec.constraint.coreconstraint

Class EqualsTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestEnvironment
      • org.apache.river.test.spec.constraint.coreconstraint.util.AbstractSimpleTest
        • org.apache.river.test.spec.constraint.coreconstraint.EqualsTest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Test, TestEnvironment

    public class EqualsTest
extends AbstractSimpleTest
    
 Purpose:
   This test verifies the behavior of the following methods:
     Object.equals(Object) for the following classes:
       ClientAuthentication
       Confidentiality
       Delegation
       Integrity
       ServerAuthentication
     ClientMaxPrincipal.equals(Object)
     ClientMaxPrincipalType.equals(Object)
     ClientMinPrincipal.equals(Object)
     ClientMinPrincipalType.equals(Object)
     ConnectionAbsoluteTime.equals(Object)
     ConnectionRelativeTime.equals(Object)
     ConstraintAlternatives.equals(Object)
     DelegationAbsoluteTime.equals(Object)
     DelegationRelativeTime.equals(Object)
     InvocationConstraints.equals(Object)
     ServerMinPrincipal.equals(Object)
   All of these methods should return true for equal objects and false for
   non-equal object. The following verifications are performed for each
   equals() method:
     - the method for the same object returns true;
     - the method for equal objects returns true;
     - the method for different (non-equal) objects returns false.
   For different classes equals() method has different sense according to
   the classes descriptions.

 Test Cases:
   TestCase #1
    Object.equals(Object) for
    ClientAuthentication objects
   TestCase #2
    ClientMaxPrincipal.equals(Object)
   TestCase #3
    ClientMaxPrincipalType.equals(Object)
   TestCase #4
    ClientMinPrincipal.equals(Object)
   TestCase #5
    ClientMinPrincipalType.equals(Object)
   TestCase #6
    Object.equals(Object) for
    Confidentiality objects
   TestCase #7
    ConnectionAbsoluteTime.equals(Object)
   TestCase #8
    ConnectionRelativeTime.equals(Object)
   TestCase #9
    ConstraintAlternatives.equals(Object)
   TestCase #10
    Object.equals(Object) for
    Delegation objects
   TestCase #11
    DelegationAbsoluteTime.equals(Object)
   TestCase #12
    DelegationRelativeTime.equals(Object)
   TestCase #13
    Object.equals(Object) for
    Integrity objects
   TestCase #14
    InvocationConstraints.equals(Object)
   TestCase #15
    Object.equals(Object) for
    ServerAuthentication objects
   TestCase #16
    ServerMinPrincipal.equals(Object)

 Infrastructure:
     - EqualsTest
         performs actions; this file
     - AbstractSimpleTest
         auxiliary abstract class that contains run() method and is
         extended by EqualsTest

 Actions:
   Test performs the following steps in each Test Case:
     - creating 3 objects of the corresponding type;
     - invoking checker(Object,Object,Object) method to verify
       the corresponding equals() method, i.e. that:
         - the method for the same object returns true;
         - the method for equal objects returns true;
         - the method for different (non-equal) objects returns false.

        public boolean checker(Object primObj,
                       Object equalObj,

        This method verifies equals() method on the objects specified as arguments. All checks to be performed are specified in the class description. This method returns true if equals() method runs correctly.
        Specified by:
        checker in class AbstractSimpleTest
        Parameters:
        primObj - the primary object
        equalObj - object that is equal to the primary object
        diffObj - object that isn't equal to the primary object
        Returns:
        true if all checks for equals() method are satisfied or false otherwise
